Geography of the Human Realms
The main human continent is called Veloria (named after the fallen Vel’thorne Empire). It is massive — roughly the size of Eurasia on Earth — stretching from frozen northern tundra to steaming southern jungles. The continent is bordered to the east and southeast by demonic territories, to the west by the Great Ocean, to the north by harsh frostlands and minor Beastkin territories, and to the south by dense rainforests and elven enclaves.
Due to 9,000 years of near-constant warfare, loss of Golden Age technology, monster infestations, demonic incursions, banditry, and unstable borders, the overall economy is stagnant to declining. Most wealth is concentrated in the hands of nobility, merchant guilds, and war profiteers. Large-scale infrastructure is rare, famines are common in war-torn regions, and trade is heavily guarded and expensive. Only a few central and coastal realms enjoy relative prosperity.
Total human population on Veloria: ~150 million (spread across 15 Kingdoms and 12 Grand Duchies).

