Overall Economic Situation Summary

Wealthy / Prosperous (≈ 15–20% of population): Central and coastal regions benefit from trade and agriculture.
Stable (≈ 30%): Mining, horse breeding, and strong defensive positions.
Struggling / Poor (≈ 50%+): Border regions suffer constant destruction, high taxes, conscription, monster attacks, and disrupted trade routes.
Major problems: Inflation, food shortages during wartime, destroyed farmlands, banditry on roads, and the enormous cost of maintaining marcher walls and armies.
The Azure Accord (merchant guild) and war profiteers are the biggest winners in this broken economy.

General Geography & Climate Overview

Northern Regions (Frostwatch, Stormcrown, parts of Ironmarch): Cold, coniferous forests, tundra, harsh winters.
Central Heartlands (Vaelor, Redfields, Whitestone): Fertile plains, rolling hills, temperate climate — the breadbasket of humanity.
Eastern Marches (Ironmarch, Ashenmarch, Blackroot, Ravenwood, Bloodfen): Rugged, scarred, and dangerous. Frequent demonic raids. Landscape features ruined cities, corrupted forests, and fortified marcher walls.
Western & Southern Coasts (Duskshore, Goldenshore, Solace): Mild Mediterranean to subtropical, major trade ports.
Mountain Ranges: The Worldspine (north-central) and Black Teeth (east) form natural barriers.
Major Rivers: The Vaelor River (lifeblood of the heartlands) and the Ironflow (eastern border river, often contested).

Quick Notes on Rulers

Most rulers come from ancient noble bloodlines claiming descent from the Vel’thorne Empire.
Succession is usually hereditary, but border kingdoms often see coups, assassinations, or “strongman” takeovers.
Several rulers (especially on the demonic border) are highly militaristic and war-focused.
